<chapter condition="TITLE=System Features: User Maintenance;ACCESS=BA_USER"
         role="TOPIC">
  <title>User Maintenance</title>

  <section condition="TITLE=System Features: User Maintenance;PERM=access_user_mc"
           id="BUM" role="TOPIC">
    <title>Overview</title>

    <para role="TEXT">As an administrator at a bank, you use the <application
    moreinfo="none">User Maintenance</application> module to create, modify or
    delete user accounts at your bank, define the permissions granted to those
    users, and reset user passwords.</para>
  </section>

  <section role="ITEM">
    <title>Terminology</title>

    <para role="TEXT">The term "account" is used in the sense it is normally
    used in software, to mean a user's registration with a system enabling him
    or her to log in - not in the everyday banking sense of a place to keep
    money.</para>
  </section>

  <section role="ITEM">
    <title>User Maintenance - Navigation</title>

    <para role="TEXT">To navigate to the <emphasis role="bold">User
    Maintenance</emphasis> function, from the toolbar, select <emphasis>System
    Features</emphasis> from the home page, then select <emphasis>User
    Maintenance</emphasis> from the left side navigation menu.</para>
  </section>

  <section role="ITEM">
    <title>User Maintenance Options</title>

    <para role="TEXT">The User Maintenance options are part of the System
    Features menu. They are as follows:</para>

    <variablelist role="TEXT">
      <varlistentry>
        <term><guimenuitem moreinfo="none">Profiles</guimenuitem>:</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>Maintain bank user accounts. A user's account details are
          called his or her profile. You can create new accounts, update
          existing accounts, and delete existing accounts. You cannot delete
          your own account. When you create a new bank user account, you are
          then shown a link to set up the user's permissions.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term><guimenuitem
        moreinfo="none">Authentication</guimenuitem>:</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>Reset user passwords.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </section>

  <section role="ITEM">
    <title>User Maintenance - Profiles</title>

    <para role="TEXT">Maintain user accounts. A user's account details are
    called his or her profile.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">When you select this option, you are presented with a
    list of all the existing user accounts at your bank. You can search the
    list by entering search criteria in the <guilabel moreinfo="none">Last
    Name</guilabel>, <guilabel moreinfo="none">First Name</guilabel> and
    <guilabel moreinfo="none">Login</guilabel> fields at the top of the
    page.</para>

    <note>
      <para>The <guilabel>Status</guilabel> and <guilabel>Maker
      User</guilabel> fields are available if maker-checker functionality is
      enabled.</para>
    </note>

    <para role="TEXT">The list of existing user accounts has the following
    columns:</para>

    <informaltable role="TEXT">
      <tgroup cols="2">
        <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="2.0*"/>

        <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="8.0*"/>

        <thead>
          <row>
            <entry valign="top"><para>Field</para></entry>

            <entry valign="top"><para>Description</para></entry>
          </row>
        </thead>

        <tbody>
          <row>
            <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel moreinfo="none">Last Name,
            First Name</guilabel> </para></entry>

            <entry valign="top"><para>First Name and Last Name of the
            user.</para></entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel
            moreinfo="none">Login</guilabel> </para></entry>

            <entry valign="top"><para>Login Id used by the user to log into
            <xi:include href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_appli"
            xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"/>. This login Id
            uniquely identifies a user account within the bank.</para></entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry
            valign="top"><para><guilabel>Status</guilabel></para></entry>

            <entry valign="top"><para>This indicates the status of the pending
            record set by the checker. </para><note>
                <para>This column is only available if maker-checker
                functionality is enabled.</para>
              </note></entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry valign="top"><para><guilabel>Maker User
            </guilabel></para></entry>

            <entry valign="top"><para>Displays the user ID of the maker of the
            transaction.</para><note>
                <para>This column is only available if maker-checker
                functionality is enabled.</para>
              </note></entry>
          </row>
        </tbody>
      </tgroup>
    </informaltable>

    <para role="TEXT">You can modify an account by clicking the <guiicon
    moreinfo="none">Edit</guiicon> <inlinemediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="../images/icon_edit.gif" role="ICON_EDIT"
                     width="4mm"/>
        </imageobject>
      </inlinemediaobject> icon in the right-hand column, view it in
    non-editable mode by clicking the <guibutton>View</guibutton>
    <inlinemediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="../images/icon_popup.gif" role="ICON_POPUP"
                     width="4.5mm"/>
        </imageobject>
      </inlinemediaobject> icon, or delete it by clicking the <guibutton
    moreinfo="none">Delete</guibutton> <inlinemediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="../images/icon_trash.gif" role="ICON_TRASH"
                     width="4mm"/>
        </imageobject>
      </inlinemediaobject> icon.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">You cannot delete your own account. A bank's main
    default administrator account <literal>bankadmin</literal> cannot be
    deleted at all. Therefore the entries for these accounts do not have the
    <guibutton moreinfo="none">Delete</guibutton> <inlinemediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="../images/icon_trash.gif" role="ICON_TRASH"
                     width="4mm"/>
        </imageobject>
      </inlinemediaobject> icon.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">Click the <guibutton moreinfo="none">Add a new
    user</guibutton> button at the bottom of the list to add an
    account.</para>

    <para role="TEXT"><guiicon moreinfo="none">Edit</guiicon> and <guibutton
    moreinfo="none">Add</guibutton> display the same form, but in the case of
    <guibutton moreinfo="none">Add</guibutton> it is blank (except that the
    <emphasis role="bold">Company</emphasis> is set to your bank) and in the
    case of <guibutton moreinfo="none">Edit</guibutton> it is preset with the
    existing details of the user's account. After entering the details, click
    <emphasis role="bold">Submit</emphasis> at the bottom of the form.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">The form is as follows:</para>

    <section role="ITEM">
      <title>Profiles Form - Main Details</title>

      <para>The Clone User checkbox enables a user to clone an existing user
      profile.<note>
          <para>The selected user profile is cloned barring the Login ID and
          Password.</para>
        </note></para>

      <para role="TEXT">The Main Details section of the form is as follows:
