  <section role="ITEM">
    <title>User Maintenance - Authentication</title>

    <note role="TEXT">
      <para>Access to this module must be given with care, and only to the
      password administrator.</para>
    </note>

    <para role="TEXT">Reset users' passwords. This is especially useful
    whenever a user has forgotten his or her password.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">When you select this option, you are presented with a
    list of all the existing user accounts at your bank. You can search the
    list by entering search criteria in the <guilabel moreinfo="none">Last
    Name</guilabel>, <guilabel moreinfo="none">First Name</guilabel> and
    <guilabel moreinfo="none">Login</guilabel> fields at the top of the
    page.</para>

    <note>
      <para>The <guilabel>Status</guilabel> and <guilabel>Maker
      User</guilabel> fields are available if maker-checker functionality is
      enabled.</para>
    </note>

    <para role="TEXT">The list of existing user accounts has the following
    columns:</para>

    <informaltable role="TEXT">
      <tgroup cols="2">
        <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="2.0*"/>

        <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="8.0*"/>

        <thead>
          <row>
            <entry valign="top"><para>Field</para></entry>

            <entry valign="top"><para>Description</para></entry>
          </row>
        </thead>

        <tbody>
          <row>
            <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel moreinfo="none">Last Name,
            First Name</guilabel> </para></entry>

            <entry valign="top"><para>First Name and Last Name of the
            user.</para></entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel
            moreinfo="none">Login</guilabel> </para></entry>

            <entry valign="top"><para>Login Id used by the user to log into
            <xi:include href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_appli"
            xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"/>. This login Id
            uniquely identifies a user account within the bank.</para></entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry
            valign="top"><para><guilabel>Status</guilabel></para></entry>

            <entry valign="top"><para>This indicates the status of the pending
            record set by the checker. </para><note>
                <para>This column is only available if maker-checker
                functionality is enabled.</para>
              </note></entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry valign="top"><para><guilabel>Maker User
            </guilabel></para></entry>

            <entry valign="top"><para>Displays the user ID of the maker of the
            transaction.</para><note>
                <para>This column is only available if maker-checker
                functionality is enabled.</para>
              </note></entry>
          </row>
        </tbody>
      </tgroup>
    </informaltable>

    <para role="TEXT">You can modify a user's password by clicking the
    <guiicon moreinfo="none">Edit</guiicon> <inlinemediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="../images/icon_edit.gif" role="ICON_EDIT"
                     width="4mm"/>
        </imageobject>
      </inlinemediaobject> icon in the right-hand column.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">You cannot add or delete users via this list - you can
    only add or delete users by using the <emphasis role="bold">User
    Maintenance - Profiles</emphasis> function.</para>

    <section role="ITEM">
      <title>Authentication Form</title>

      <para role="TEXT">When you click the <guiicon
      moreinfo="none">Edit</guiicon> <inlinemediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="../images/icon_edit.gif" role="ICON_EDIT"
                       width="4mm"/>
          </imageobject>
        </inlinemediaobject> icon, you get the following form.</para>

      <para role="TEXT">After entering the details, click <emphasis
      role="bold">Submit</emphasis> at the bottom of the form. The changes
      take effect the next time the user logs in to <xi:include
      href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_appli"
      xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"/>.</para>

      <para role="TEXT">When the password is changed, the password expiry date
      is computed and stored, and the counter of invalid login attempts is
      reset. The user is also re-activated if previously inactive.</para>

      <informaltable role="TEXT">
        <tgroup cols="3">
          <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="2.0*"/>

          <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="1.0*"/>

          <colspec colname="c3" colwidth="6.0*"/>

          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para>Field</para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>Type</para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>Description</para></entry>
            </row>
          </thead>

          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel
              moreinfo="none">Company</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para> <inlinemediaobject>
                  <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="../images/char_info.gif"
                               role="CHAR_INFO" width="4mm"/>
                  </imageobject>
                </inlinemediaobject> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>Bank's abbreviated name that is part
              of the user identification in <xi:include
              href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_appli"
              xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"/>.</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel moreinfo="none">Login
              Id</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para> <inlinemediaobject>
                  <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="../images/char_info.gif"
                               role="CHAR_INFO" width="4mm"/>
                  </imageobject>
                </inlinemediaobject> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>Login Id that the user uses to log
              into <xi:include href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_appli"
              xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"/>.</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel
              moreinfo="none">Name</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para> <inlinemediaobject>
                  <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="../images/char_info.gif"
                               role="CHAR_INFO" width="4mm"/>
                  </imageobject>
                </inlinemediaobject> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>First Name and Last Name of the
              user.</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel
              moreinfo="none">Password</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para> <inlinemediaobject>
                  <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="../images/char_excla.gif"
                               role="CHAR_EXCLA" width="2mm"/>
                  </imageobject>
                </inlinemediaobject> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>New password. <note>
                  <para><orderedlist>
                      <listitem>
                        <para>The password policy, which defines the maximum
                        and minimum length of the password, the characters
                        accepted, and the combination of characters, is set up
                        in the system by your administrator.</para>
                      </listitem>

                      <listitem>
                        <para>This field is not displayed if the auto-password
                        generation feature is enabled for your Bank.</para>
                      </listitem>
                    </orderedlist></para>
                </note></para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel moreinfo="none">Confirm
              Password</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para> <inlinemediaobject>
                  <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="../images/char_excla.gif"
                               role="CHAR_EXCLA" width="2mm"/>
                  </imageobject>
                </inlinemediaobject> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>Retype the new password.</para><note>
                  <para>This field is not displayed if the auto-password
                  generation feature is enabled for your Bank.</para>
                </note></entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </informaltable>
